# Chat / session title carries backlog id

When the conversation is about a **tracked backlog item** (GitHub issue / story),
the chat or session title must include that id so the board and the conversation
stay aligned.

## When

- Starting work on an issue (`#342`, `GH-327`, board card, task-prompt `story_id`)
- Switching focus to a different issue mid-chat
- Starting `/rabbit-loop` or a `task/*` implementation pass tied to an issue

## Format

```text
#<github-issue> · <≤6 word topic>
```

Prefer the **GitHub issue number** (`#342`) over the story id (`GH-222`) when
they differ — same rule as PR bodies in `AGENTS.md`. If only a story id exists
yet, use `GH-NNN · topic` until the issue is filed.

Use the preflight suggestion when present (`suggested_chat_title` /
`--chat-summary` § Chat title).

## How (this agent)

Follow **`docs/skills/session-title-adapters.md`** for the product you are in:

- **Cursor:** MCP `rename_chat` (`cursor-app-control`)
- **Claude Code:** `/rename #N · topic`
- **Zed:** ask human to click-edit the Agent Panel thread title (UI-only)
- **Others:** product rename if any; else one-line `Chat title (manual): …`

## Do not

- Rename on every trivial turn
- Put private customer names in the title
- Block work if rename is unavailable (best-effort)

Also: `docs/skills/rabbit-loop.md` § Chat title.
